UNITED STATES of America v. Rose RODBERG, Appellant. No. 10511. United States Court of Appeals Third Circuit. Argued Nov. 12, 1951. Decided Nov. 27, 1951. George R. Sommer, Newark, N. J., for appellant. Charles J. Tyne, Asst. U. S. Atty., Newark, N. J., (Grover C. Richman, Jr., U. S. Atty., Newark, N. J., on the brief), for ap-pellee. ’

Before MARIS, KALODNER and STA-LEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We have carefully considered the contentions advanced .by the appellant in her brief and oral argument but find them to be without merit. The judgment of the district court will accordingly be affirmed.
